# Telegram Bot

Connect a Telegram bot so people can run `/bg` and receive alerts in Telegram. This page
covers the Telegram-specific steps; for account linking, alert delivery, and the Admin UI /
environment-variable workflow that all platforms share, see [Chat Bots](/docs/bots).

## 1. Create a bot with BotFather

1. In Telegram, open a chat with [@BotFather](https://t.me/BotFather).
2. Send `/newbot` and follow the prompts to choose a name and username.
3. BotFather replies with a **bot token** (looks like `123456:ABC-DEF...`). Copy it.

<Callout type="warning" title="Keep the token secret">
  Anyone with the bot token can control the bot. If it leaks, send <code>/revoke</code> to
  BotFather to issue a new one.
</Callout>

## 2. Configure Nocturne

Enter the token using either method (see [Chat Bots](/docs/bots) for the full workflow).

### Option A: Admin UI

At **Settings > Admin > Integrations**, fill in the **Telegram** card:

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **Bot Token** | The token from BotFather |

Turn **Enabled** on, click **Save**, and restart the Nocturne web service.

### Option B: Environment variables

```bash
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABC-DEF...
# Optional: a secret token Telegram echoes back on each webhook call so
# Nocturne can confirm the request really came from Telegram.
TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET_TOKEN=...
```

Then restart Nocturne.

## 3. Register the webhook

Telegram pushes updates to a webhook URL you register through its Bot API. Point it at your
instance:

```bash
curl "https://api.telegram.org/bot<YOUR_BOT_TOKEN>/setWebhook" \
  -d "url=https://your-instance.com/api/v4/webhooks/telegram"
```

If you set `TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET_TOKEN`, pass the same value here so Telegram includes it
on every call:

```bash
curl "https://api.telegram.org/bot<YOUR_BOT_TOKEN>/setWebhook" \
  -d "url=https://your-instance.com/api/v4/webhooks/telegram" \
  -d "secret_token=<YOUR_SECRET_TOKEN>"
```

<Callout type="tip" title="Check the webhook">
  Confirm it registered with
  <code>https://api.telegram.org/bot&lt;YOUR_BOT_TOKEN&gt;/getWebhookInfo</code>. The
  <code>url</code> should match your instance and <code>last_error_message</code> should be
  empty.
</Callout>

## 4. Test it

1. Open a chat with your bot in Telegram and send `/connect`, then complete the link.
2. Send `/bg` and confirm the latest reading comes back.
